g each other and laugh face to face. The adult’s arms wrap around the child, and the child nestles against the adult’s side.\n\nA close-up of two hands clasping appears in golden sunlight. Large pale-yellow text overlays the image, first reading “JUST,” then “JUST TWO,” and finally “JUST TWO DAYS,” with a small asterisk after “DAYS.” Tiny fine print appears near the bottom but is too small to read clearly.\n\nThe product returns in a home-like setting. The Gold Bond Crepe Corrector tube stands upright in sharp focus on the right side of a surface. Behind it, blurred, an adult in a sleeveless white top rubs lotion onto their upper arm and shoulder. The background is softly lit and warm, with hints of household objects and greenery. Small on-screen text near the bottom reads “Use as directed.”\n\nA group of Gold Bond products is arranged on stepped teal blocks: the main Crepe Corrector tube stands at the left, a smaller matching tube stands behind it, a white pump bottle labeled Gold Bond is at the right, and two additional tubes lie angled across the foreground. The packaging shares the same white, purple, and gold color scheme. “Use as directed” remains in small text near the bottom.\n\nFinally, the product arrangement darkens into the background as oversized pale-yellow words fill the screen. The text appears in sequence: “CHAMPION,” then “CHAMPION YOUR,” and then “CHAMPION YOUR SKIN,” echoing the Gold Bond slogan while the products remain faintly visible behind the letters.",
